DOCUMENT();
loadMacros("PG.pl",
           "PGbasicmacros.pl",
           "PGchoicemacros.pl",
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
           "PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl",
           "Dartmouthmacros.pl");
 

## Do NOT show partial correct answers
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

## Lots of set up goes here


## Ok, we are ready to begin the problem...
##
TEXT(beginproblem());

$a = random( 1, 4, 1 );
$b = random( 1, 4, 1 );
$c = random( 1, 4, 1 );

$ans1 = "1/y";
$ans2 = "-x/(y**2) + 1/z";
$ans3 = "-y/(z**2)";
$ans4 = sqrt( 1/($b**2) + ( -($a/($b**2)) + (1/$c) )**2 + (- $b/($c**2))**2 );

BEGIN_TEXT

Suppose \( f \left( x, y, z \right) = \frac{x}{y} + \frac{y}{z} \), \(
P = \left( $a, $b, $c \right) \).

$PAR

A. Find the gradient of f (at the point (x,y,z)). $BR \( \nabla f = (\) \{ans_rule(19)\},
 \{ans_rule(19)\},\{ans_rule(19)\} \( ) \)

$BR
Note: Your answers should be expressions of x, y and z; e.g. ${LQ}3x - 4yz${RQ}

$PAR

B. What is the maximum rate of change of f at the point P? $BR
\{ans_rule(40)\} $BR
Note: Your answer should be a number
END_TEXT

ANS( multivar_function_cmp( $ans1, 3 ) );
ANS( multivar_function_cmp( $ans2, 3 ) );
ANS( multivar_function_cmp( $ans3, 3 ) );
ANS( std_num_cmp( $ans4 ) );

ENDDOCUMENT();




